Document Review & Corrections (v1.1)

Reviewed 2026-05-14 against the BRD, UX Architecture, System Architecture, Database Architecture, and project instructions. Strategic content preserved; the following clarifications and corrections apply and override earlier text where they conflict.

1. "Dynamic pricing" clarification. Where this document lists "Dynamic pricing" under the Booking Engine, it means admin-configurable pricing rules (fixed price or supplier cost + markup, configurable per airport/service — see DECISIONS.md D-008). It does NOT mean AI/algorithmic dynamic pricing, which is explicitly post-MVP.

2. Payment provider is Stripe. Wherever a generic "payment gateway" is referenced, the canonical provider for MVP is Stripe (Payment Intents, webhooks, multi-currency, refunds/partial refunds). See DECISIONS.md D-001.

3. Commercial model. AirportFaster operates as merchant of record: it collects the full customer payment and settles suppliers separately (DECISIONS.md D-006). The customer is charged at checkout (D-007).

4. Roles. The canonical role set is seven: Super Admin, Operations, Customer Support, Finance, Supplier Manager, Content & SEO, Analyst. Earlier lists in this document that omit "Analyst" are superseded.

5. AI content. AI-assisted SEO and translation draft systems ARE in MVP scope (draft-only, never auto-publish; Draft → Review → Edit → Approve → Publish). "AI-generated content workflows (future)" in the CMS section is updated: the draft workflow is MVP; only fully automated AI operations are post-MVP.

6. Tech stack specifics. Canonical choices: backend = Fastify; ORM = Prisma. "Express" and "Drizzle" alternatives in this document are non-canonical.

7. The complete, current architecture is captured across AGENTS.md, the System Architecture Document, and the Database Architecture & Entity Relationship Design. This PAD remains the source of truth for brand, vision, positioning, and business strategy.